It was quiet at night and although a little hot (There was a bit of a heatwave) the hotel provided a fan in the room.	My only concern was that the rooms were a little hot - they do provide a fan though.	For people who are planning to visit in summer, you might want to know that there is no air-condition or fan in the room and it can be quite noisy in the street if you open up the windows.	We slept with a fan running and windows open (into an interior well between buildings.)